# ðŸ§ª Landing Page â€“ Test Plan

---

## 1. Objective
Ensure that the Landing Page functions correctly, provides a smooth user experience,
is accessible, responsive, performant, secure, and ready for production release.

---

## 2. Scope

### In Scope
- Landing Page UI elements
- Header and Footer visibility
- Navigation links (Categories, CTA, Search access)
- Authentication links visibility (Login / Register / Logout)
- Cart, Wishlist, Currency selector (access only)
- Responsiveness & Accessibility
- Integration with other pages
- Performance, Security, SEO (technical)

### Out of Scope
- Login / Register validation logic
- Cart / Wishlist backend logic
- Checkout & payment flow
- Order placement

---

## 3. Test Types
- Functional Testing
- Integration Testing
- Usability Testing
- Accessibility Testing
- Compatibility Testing
- Performance Testing
- Security Testing
- API Testing
- SEO Testing (Technical)

---

## 4. Test Environment
- Browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Safari
- Devices: Desktop, Tablet, Mobile
- OS: Windows, macOS, Android, iOS
- Network: WiFi, Mobile Data, Offline mode

---

## 5. Entry Criteria
- Landing Page deployed
- UI design approved
- APIs available and stable

---

## 6. Exit Criteria
- All critical and high-priority test cases passed
- No blocker or critical defects open
- Performance and accessibility requirements met

---

## 7. Risks
- API instability affecting landing page elements
- Performance degradation on mobile devices
- Accessibility gaps impacting usability

---

## 8. Deliverables
- Test Cases document
- Bug reports
- Test summary report

